com.esri.mo2.map.dpy
Interface LayerExtension

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable
All Known Subinterfaces:
ExtractExtension, GeoCodeExtension, StoredQueryExtension
All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseExtractExtension, BaseGeoCodeExtension, BaseLayerExtension, BaseStoredQueryExtension
public interface LayerExtension
extends Cloneable

Defines an optional functionality that can be added to a Layer at run-time. One or more LayerExtensions may be added to a Layer. Each is identified by an unique identity code. Certain "well known" LayerExtensions, for example geo-coding, have identity codes that are pre-defined here, however, these well-known identity codes are not reserved for any particular extension. Care must be taken when adding new extensions not to overwrite pre-existing extensions.

The main purpose of a LayerExtension object is to store the parameters that are needed to define the extension.

See Also:
Layer.setExtension(com.esri.mo2.map.dpy.LayerExtension)

getID

public String getID()
Returns the unique identity code associated with this LayerExtension object. Certain commonly-used identity codes are pre-defined here, for example GEOCODE. A LayerExtension implementation must provide its own ID code.

Returns:
the identity code
